dismissalText.commentary: Steven Smith c Salt b Rashid 94 (114b 5x4 1x6 163m) SR: 82.45

dismissalComment.html: holes out to long off! Tried to bring up his hundred with a six and fell three metres short. He skipped down to a slower leg break, he sliced this high off the toe, got a decent piece of it but not quite enough and Salt is composed on the rope to take the catch.

dismissalText.commentary: Marnus Labuschagne c Roy b Rashid 58 (55b 4x4 1x6 73m) SR: 105.45

dismissalComment.html: oh no, Labuschagne has chipped to mid-off! He almost got out right at the start of his innings to Rashid, top-edging a slog-sweep short of long-on, and he gets this attempt even more wrong... the bat seemed to jam into the pitch as he paddled across the line, and a simple catch loops tamely to mid-off. Timely breakthrough for England, after a productive stand

dismissalText.commentary: David Warner c Dawson b Ali 16 (17b 2x4 0x6 25m) SR: 94.11

dismissalComment.html: flicks a sweep straight to backward square in the ring! Dawson takes the catch moving to his left and takes it easily. He threw his head back in frustration when he saw he'd picked out Dawson

dismissalComment.html: Given lbw! Vince reviews. It was high but he was hit on the back though. It was a good length tailing into middle and off. dismissalComment.html: skied straight up to mid off! Crazy shot! England needed to settle and Curran tried to hit out. He didn't pick the wrong un as he tried to launch with mid off up, the miscue goes straight up, Hazlewood backs back and takes it comfortably.

headshotImage.caption: Liam Dawson player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Liam Dawson player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: hit on the full, given lbw! Four for Zampa. Dawson reviews but it looked pretty straight. Sliding in from over the wicket and pops him on the front pad around ankle height, only has to be clipping - and it is! Umpire's call on leg stump, and Australia have wrapped this one up with room to spare

headshotImage.caption: MA Starc headshot
headshotImage.longCaption: MA Starc headshot

headshotImage.caption: Jason Roy player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jason Roy player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: short and gloved down the leg side! Starc strikes second ball, gets Roy again. No rattle of the timbers this time, and perhaps Roy will feel he has got himself out here. Back of a length, 142kph/88mph on the hip and he gets tucked up, playing neither a pull nor a flick and getting a touch through to Carey. Up goes the finger and off walks England's senior opener

headshotImage.caption: Dawid Malan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dawid Malan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: bowled 'im! Beauty from Starc, England are 0 for 2! Another sizzling outswinger, this time at 146kph/91mph, and it turns Malan inside out before slamming into the top of off. Beautiful line, straightening from middle and off, plenty of heat on the ball and Malan was nowhere near it, looking to clip through the on side as the as the ominous "thunk" came from behind him

headshotImage.caption: CR Woakes headshot
headshotImage.longCaption: CR Woakes headshot

dismissalComment.html: splat go the timbers! Starc rips through Woakes, angling in from round the wicket and through a flaccid forward prod. Maybe just straightening past the outside edge. Took some tap in that over, but Starc hits the right areas and moves Australia to within two wickets of victory

headshotImage.caption: David Willey player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: David Willey player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: dragged on, no kicking this away! Back of a length from over the wicket, gets big and cramps Willey for room as he attempts to punch off the back foot. Comes off the inside edge and then off the body into the stumps... Willey tosses his bat in frustration, and this really might just be that for England's hopes

Sliding in from over the wicket and pops him on the front pad around ankle height, only has to be clipping - and it is! Umpire's call on leg stump, and Australia have wrapped this one up with room to spare

commentPreTextItems.html: Here's Matt Leonard: "Can confirm, that while this series defeat is slightly annoying, the overriding emotion is 'Meh, they're probably still groggy from last Sunday, whose decision was this series anyway?'"

commentTextItems.html: hit on the full, given lbw! Four for Zampa. Dawson reviews but it looked pretty straight. Sliding in from over the wicket and pops him on the front pad around ankle height, only has to be clipping - and it is! Umpire's call on leg stump, and Australia have wrapped this one up with room to spare

commentPostTextItems.html: 9.50pm: Here's Adam Zampa, talking to BT Sport: "It's a series win, that's important to us against a good England side. Vince and Billings today, looked like it was going to be tough but we got a couple of big wickets. It was a hard wicket to start on. It was going to swing early, we felt the wicket was up and down. Knew reverse swing would come in later, and we made it tough for them. We're disappointed with how the World Cup went, England deserved to win but it's nice to get this series."

Mitchell Starc was named Player of the Match, meanwhile, but BT elected not to show the presentations from the SCG - so you'll just have to imagine how Josh Hazlewood described his captaincy debut (or better yet, stick around on the site and wait for Gnasher to file). His report will be in the slot here shortly, and we'll be back for the culmination of England's tour down under, live from the MCG next week. Thanks for your comments, from myself, Alex and Raghav, it's goodbye. Bye!

9.38pm: A hefty margin of victory in the end, belying the fact England seemed well on top of the requirement when James Vince and Sam Billings were going along. Victory puts Australia 2-0 up with one game left in the series, in Melbourne on Tuesday. We suggested at halfway that their 280, underpinned by 94 from Steven Smith, looked a challenging total, and it proved to be the case

commentPreTextItems.html: "Let's not get carried away with what England C achieved against Pakistan," muses Robert. "That was at home with a team full of experienced county players in mid season. This is an experienced side but it's away against the Aussies best 11 with half a team who have just won a WC and half rusty. It would be a challenge for the England first XI."

commentTextItems.html: dragged on, no kicking this away! Back of a length from over the wicket, gets big and cramps Willey for room as he attempts to punch off the back foot. Comes off the inside edge and then off the body into the stumps... Willey tosses his bat in frustration, and this really might just be that for England's hopes

dismissalText.commentary: James Vince lbw b Hazlewood 60 (72b 3x4 2x6 118m) SR: 83.33

dismissalComment.html: Given lbw! Vince reviews. It was high but he was hit on the back though. It was a good length tailing into middle and off. Umpire's call on hitting so England keep the review but he was hitting a fair bit of middle.

dismissalText.commentary: Liam Dawson lbw b Zampa 20 (21b 1x4 1x6 39m) SR: 95.23

dismissalComment.html: hit on the full, given lbw! Four for Zampa. Dawson reviews but it looked pretty straight. Sliding in from over the wicket and pops him on the front pad around ankle height, only has to be clipping - and it is! Umpire's call on leg stump, and Australia have wrapped this one up with room to spare
